subSubSection.paragraph:
Collophore (
Fig. 31A
). Anterior side with about 12–13 ciliate chaetae, 3 proximal elongated chaetae, 6 thin chaetae of different sizes widely distributed on tube and 3–4 distal chaetae (2–4 mac); posterior side with about 16 ciliate chaetae (3 unpaired), 1 larger unpaired median mac, proximal half with 6 elongated chaetae and distal half with 7 mes (2 unpaired) subequal in length, distally 3 ciliate chaetae, no smooth chaetae; lateral flap with about 10 chaetae, 5 smooth and 5 ciliate.

